<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1398" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1398">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/616.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Agent <persName type="to">Silliman</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>St. Louis and Oaxaca Iron and Steel Company, American concern, reports it
                            bought seven years ago for $33,000 gold, iron and timber lands State
                            Oaxaca located seventy-five miles from railroad, undeveloped and only
                            potential value; have never paid any revenue; annual tax heretofore $750
                            gold; annual tax now imposed $14,000 gold.</p>
                        <p>Bring to attention appropriate authorities; request to be informed
                            whether State Oaxaca under their control and if so what action they
                            intend to take with reference to this clearly confiscatory tax.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>